<i>noun</i>: 행사 [행사], 의식 [의식], 의례 [의례], 예식 [예식], 예 [예], 식 [식] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>행사 [행사]</dt><br>
<dd>event; occasion; ceremony</dd><br>
<dd>목적이나 계획을 가지고 절차에 따라서 어떤 일을 시행함. 또는 그 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of performing a certain task with a purpose or plan according to a procedure; or such a task.</dd><br>
<dt>의식 [의식]</dt><br>
<dd>ceremony; function</dd><br>
<dd>정해진 방법이나 절차에 따라 치르는 행사.</dd><br>
<dd>An event carried out according to a certain manner and procedure.</dd><br>
<dt>의례 [의례]</dt><br>
<dd>formality; ceremony; courtesy</dd><br>
<dd>행사를 치르는 일정한 형식과 절차. 또는 정해진 형식과 절차에 따라 치르는 행사.</dd><br>
<dd>A certain manner and procedure for carrying out an event; an event carried out according to a certain manner and procedure.</dd><br>
<dt>예식 [예식]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ceremony</dd><br>
<dd>예의와 규범에 따라 행하는 의식.</dd><br>
<dd>A ritual performed according to certain manners and rules.</dd><br>
<dd>2. wedding</dd><br>
<dd>성인 남녀가 법적으로 부부가 됨을 알리는 의식.</dd><br>
<dd>A ceremony for announcing that an adult man and woman become husband and wife legally.</dd><br>
<dt>예 [예]</dt><br>
<dd>1. politeness; courtesy</dd><br>
<dd>사람이 당연히 지켜야 할 바른 마음가짐과 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>Good mental attitude and manners that a person should keep.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ceremony</dd><br>
<dd>예의와 규범에 따라 행하는 의식.</dd><br>
<dd>A ritual performed according to certain manners and rules.</dd><br>
<dd>3. etiquette; decorum</dd><br>
<dd>예의로써 지켜야 할 규칙.</dd><br>
<dd>Rules that should be followed as manners.</dd><br>
<dt>식 [식]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ceremony; ritual</dd><br>
<dd>정해진 방식에 따라 치르는 행사.</dd><br>
<dd>An event performed according to a certain format.</dd><br>
<dd>2. expression</dd><br>
<dd>수학에서, 숫자, 문자, 기호 등을 써서 어떤 방법을 설명하는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>In math, the act of explaining a certain method using numbers, letters, signs, etc.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>